      "writtenOn": "2015-09-08T06:38:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You must know that local_settings are not imported anywhere. And such file is a good place to control application (ansible templates). Another option is to:\n\nimport local_settings as settings\n\n# and use settings.CONSTANT\n\nand in local_settings:\n\nfrom django.conf import settings\n\nCONSTANT \u003d getattr(settings, \u0027CONSTANT\u0027, \u0027default\u0027)",
      "parentUuid": "da20952f_770715ca",
      "revId": "2abb46c62a576d546294515b06d6bf73611d966a",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
